Abuja (Post) – Octogenarian and constitutional lawyer, Professor
Ben Nwabueze (SAN) appeared briefly before the Presidential Election Petition
Tribunal (PEPT) in Abuja, announcing himself as the leader of the Atiku
Abubakar’s legal team. Prof Nwabueze, who came in on a wheelchair, on Thursday morning
read a prepared speech before the commencement of proceedings and then left
shortly after. The Elder Statesman who spoke to the Tribunal for a while on his
seat said he had to appear in the proceeding to send a strong message about the
importance of the case for Nigeria’s democratic development. Details shortly…